We can use CLI (Command Line Interface) or Graphical User Interface (GUI) when using Linux. 

OpenSUSE uses KDE instead of GNOME.

GNOME Desktop Environment
===========================

KDE is used by OpenSUSE
GNOME is used by Debian Family
Other desktop environment include unity, Xfce, LXDE

GUI startup
===========
The default display manager for GNOME is called gdm 
Other popular display managers include lightdm & kdm


Locking screen
===============
keyboard shortcut ctrl+alt+L

viewing files
=============
Nautilus is the file manager of file browser
ctrl-1, ctrl-2, ctrl-3

show hidden files ctrl+h
nautilus : alt+f2
search textbox: ctrl+f
specific directory access: ctrl-L

Removing a file
===============
Deleting a file in nautils will automatically move the deleted files to the 
.local/share/Trash/files

Default directories under Home are Desktop, Documents, Downloads


Summary:
========

GNOME is a popular desktop environment and graphical user interface that runs on the top of 
the Linux OS.
The default display manager for GNOME is called gdm
The gdm display manager presents the user with login screen which prompts user name and password.

Logging out through the desktop environment kills all processes in your current X-session and returns to the display manager login screen.

Every user created in the system will have a home directory 
Each linux distribution comes with its own set of desktop backgrounds

